qMetaDef.title: Unused Sheets (90 Days)

qMeasure.qDef:
Num(Sum(
		Aggr(
			Count({$<[App Object Type]={"Sheet"}>-<AppObjectId={"=max({<[App Object Type]={'Sheet'},sheet_audit_indicator={'1'}>} LogTimeStamp) >= vLast90Days"}>} Distinct AppObjectId)
        ,ObjectId)
    )
,'#,##0')

qMetaDef.description: This is the total in-memory size of the result and data added to the cache during the period. This measures how the volume of new results, and can be used to judge if increased memory consumption is caused by request or by traffic e.g. When the memory is saturated (70—90% default), a corresponding volume of results are dropped from the cache.
qMetaDef.title: Cache Bytes Added

qMetaDef.description: Cache hits is the number of lookups of results or sub-results in the Engine’s result and data cache that was hit (found), and thus re-used without needing calculation. Not all stages of a given task uses the cache and usually needs some additional processing before the result is complete, so even Cache hits result in some load on the machine.
qMetaDef.title: Cache Hits
